# Script, CI/CD workflow, and deploy JSON style

Reference entrypoint: [`scripts/cd/azure-cd-inject-secrets.sh`](scripts/cd/azure-cd-inject-secrets.sh).

## Bash entrypoints (`scripts/**/*.sh`)

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

ROOT="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")/.." && pwd)"   # adjust ../ depth
LOG_PREFIX="[DEPLOY]"   # see prefix table below
# shellcheck source=scripts/shared/common.sh
source "$ROOT/scripts/shared/common.sh"

require_env REQUIRED_VAR

############################################
log_step "SECTION NAME IN ALL CAPS"
```

| Rule | Convention |
|------|------------|
| Strict mode | `set -euo pipefail` on line 2, or after a short (≤10 line) English header |
| Logging | Source [`scripts/shared/common.sh`](scripts/shared/common.sh); never redefine `log_*` / `fail`; never use `echo "==>"` |
| Sections | 44× `#` divider + `log_step "…"`; no numbered `# 1.` comments; no extra `echo "===="` frames |
| Env vars | `require_env VAR`; use `fail "message"` instead of ad-hoc `exit 1` |
| Language | English only for comments and log text |
| Output | ASCII status (`OK`), not Unicode symbols |

### `LOG_PREFIX` examples

| Scripts | Prefix |
|---------|--------|
| CD build / wait / migrate / smoke | `[DEPLOY][BUILD]`, `[DEPLOY][IMAGE]`, `[DEPLOY][MIGRATE]`, `[DEPLOY][SMOKE]` |
| CD deploy / secrets | `[DEPLOY]` |
| Infra Bicep deploy | `[DEPLOY][INFRA]` |
| CI tests / harness / versions | `[CI][TEST]`, `[CI][HARNESS]`, `[CI][VERSIONS]`, `[CI][CACHE]` |
| Dev / local tooling | `[DEV]`, `[DOTNET]`, `[MIGRATE]`, `[TEST]` |

Set `LOG_PREFIX` **before** sourcing `common.sh`.

## Bash libraries (sourced)

- `# shellcheck shell=bash` + 1–2 line English purpose comment
- No `set -euo pipefail` (inherit from caller)
- Use `log_info` / `log_warn` / `log_error` when emitting messages; caller must source `common.sh` first
- `# shellcheck source=…` on every `source` in entrypoints

## Container entrypoints (`infra/**` — exception)

Keep `#!/bin/sh`, POSIX-only, no bash `common.sh`. English comments, `set -e`, minimal headers.

## CI and CD workflows ([`ci-v2.yml`](.github/workflows/ci-v2.yml), [`cd-v1.yml`](.github/workflows/cd-v1.yml))

Shared conventions:

- Numbered section banners `# 0.` … `# N.` with 44× `#` dividers (workflow owns numbering; scripts do not)
- Blank line after `steps:`
- 6-space indent under `steps:`
- Every step has a `name:` (including checkout)
- Step `name:` aligns with banner titles (Title Case, descriptive)
- Reuse workflow `env:` variables (e.g. `${{ env.COMPOSE_ENV_FILE }}`) instead of duplicating paths
- English-only comments and step names
- Gate/summary steps use bracketed tags (`[CI][FAILURE]`, `[DEPLOY][SUCCESS]`)

CI job section pattern (rust, web, api, harness):

| # | Banner |
|---|--------|
| 0 | CHECKOUT |
| 1 | RENDER VERSIONS |
| 2 | LOAD VERSIONS |
| 3 | CACHE … |
| 4+ | Job-specific (tests, Buildx, harness) |

## Parameter JSON (`infra/azure/parameters*.json`)

JSON has no inline comments; document intent in [`infra/azure/README.md`](infra/azure/README.md).

- 2-space indent throughout
- `$schema` first; multiline `{ "value": … }` blocks
- English strings only
